hackathon-rules:
Dates: May 7th Noon to May 8th Noon           
Eligibility: Individuals, teams. High School Students to Graduate Students. Max team size: 5.
Submission Requirements: Originality. Future Impact. Functionality. Performance. Ease of Use.
Prizes & Winner Selection: 1st place dell tablets. 1 TB Hard drives for the Best Use of AWS. Swag Bags w/ Sparkfun Redboards for the Best Domain Names from Domain.com. An Octocat statue for the Best Developer Tool.
The winners of each prize will be determined by a panel of 5 judges.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: One Dell Venue 10 pro tablet for each team member.
A Dell 1TB hard drive + a Jawbone UP Activity Tracking Band for each team member.
A Dell 1TB hard drive for each team member.
A Jawbone UP Activity Tracking Band for each team member.
Swag bags including Sparkfun Redboards for each winner.
A Github Octocat Statue for each team member.
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Best use of Github Developer Tools
